Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Pop the aubergine and courgette chunks onto a large #baking tray{}, drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if you need to, you want the vegetables to be nicely spaced apart.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with 0.5 tsp @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @Vivera Plant Meatballs{200} and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside. Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with another drizzle of oil if needed and add the red onion. Cook, stirring occasionally until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1} and @tomato puree{30}g to the frying pan and season with salt and pepper. Add the @sugar{1/2} for the sauce. Simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when the vegetables have around 12 mins left, add the @linguine{200} to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the vegetables are cooked, stir them through the tomato sauce along with the browned meatballs, adding a splash of water if you need to. Bring to a simmer and cook until everything is piping hot. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Drain the linguine in a #colander{} and add to the meatball sauce with half the parsley, stirring well so that everything is evenly mixed together. Divide between your bowls and top with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!